# Package Management Rules

## Package Manager: npm

This project uses **npm** as the package manager. Never use pnpm or yarn.

### Installing Packages

**Always use the workspace flag when adding packages to specific apps or packages.**

Examples:
```bash
# Add a package to the api app
npm install stripe -w api

# Add a dev dependency to the web app
npm install -D @types/lodash -w web

# Add a package to a shared package
npm install lodash -w app-constants

# Add a package to all workspaces (root)
npm install zod -w .

# Add a dev dependency to the root workspace
npm install -D husky -w .
```

### Workspace Dependencies

When referencing internal packages, use `*` in package.json (npm workspaces resolve them):
```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "app-constants": "*",
    "shared": "*"
  }
}
```
